results.name: Number of non-isomorphic set-systems of weight n with no singletons or endpoints.
comment: A set-system is a finite set of finite nonempty set of positive integers. A singleton is an edge of size 1. An endpoint is a vertex appearing only once (degree 1). The weight of a set-system is the sum of sizes of its parts. Weight is generally not the same as number of vertices.
example: Non-isomorphic representatives of the a(7) = 1 through a(10) = 16 set-systems:
xref: Non-isomorphic set-systems with no singletons are A306005.
Non-isomorphic set-systems with no endpoints are A330054.
Non-isomorphic set-systems counted by vertices are A000612.
Non-isomorphic set-systems counted by weight are A283877.
